马达加斯加最高的几座山峰分别位于三大高原地块：[[马鲁穆库特鲁山|马鲁穆库特鲁山]]高2876米，位于[[马达加斯加地理|察拉塔纳纳山]]，是岛上的地理最高点；其后是座落在[[安德林吉特拉国家公园|安德林吉特拉国家公园]]的波比峰，高2658米；再是位于[[安卡拉特拉山|安卡拉特拉山]]上的齐亚法扎武纳山，高2643米。东部的潘加兰运河由一连串人工和天然湖泊经法国人建造的内陆运河连接而成，全长约600公里，与东部海岸线基本平行。岛的西面和南部属于中部高地的[[雨影|雨影区]]，这里有[[马达加斯加干燥落叶林|干燥落叶林]]、多刺灌木林以及沙漠和旱生灌丛。由于这些地区人口密度较低，马达加斯加的干燥落叶林与东部雨林和中部高地的原始林地相比都保存得更好。该国西海岸有很多受到保护的海港，但是，流经广阔西部平原的多条河流因内陆[[侵蚀作用|侵蚀作用]]带来大量[[沉积物|沉积物]]，给这些海港造成很大麻烦。<ref name="EBLand">{{cite web |last=Encyclopaedia Britannica |title=Madagascar |work=Encyclopaedia Britannica |publisher=Eb.com |year=2011 |url=http://global.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/355562/Madagascar |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64fD1P7X2?url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/355562/Madagascar |archivedate=2012-01-13 |accessdate=2014-05-07 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

=== 气候 ===
[[File:Biogeographic_timetable_of_Madagascar_-_journal.pone.0062086.g003.png|thumb]]
受东南[[信风|信风]]和西北[[季风|季风]]的共同影响，马达加斯加每年11月至次年4月都是炎热的雨季，并且经常会遭遇破坏性的[[气旋|气旋]]袭击，每年的5至10月则是相对较为凉爽的旱季。源于印度洋上空的雨云会在岛上东部沿海地区上空释放掉大部分湿气，充沛的降水支撑当地[[雨林|雨林]]生态系统。中部高地相比东部来说较为干燥和凉爽，西部则更为干燥，岛上的西南和南部内陆以[[半干旱气候|半干旱气候]]为主<ref name="endemicstats" />。每年都会有多场[[热带气旋|热带气旋]]吹袭马达加斯加，造成[[基础设施|基础设施]]受损和人员伤亡，对當地经济构成打击<ref name="LOC">{{cite web |last=Metz |first=Helen Chapin |year=1994 |title=Library of Congress Country Studies: Madagascar |archivedate=2013-08-26 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826103623/http://countrystudies.us/madagascar/ |deadurl=yes |url=http://countrystudies.us/madagascar/ |accessdate=2014-05-07 }}</ref>。2004年，[[气旋加菲洛|气旋加菲洛]]成为[[信史|有纪录以来]]袭击该国的最强气旋，造成172人死亡，21万4260人流离失所<ref name="gafilo">{{cite web | author = International Federation of Red Cross And Red Crescent Societies | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2005-02-25 | archivedate = 2014-01-10 | title = Madagascar: Cyclone Gafilo, Final Report, Appeal 08/04 | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140110075934/http://reliefweb.int/report/madagascar/madagascar-cyclone-gafilo-final-report-appeal-0804 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/madagascar/madagascar-cyclone-gafilo-final-report-appeal-0804 }}</ref>，经济损失超过2.5亿美元<ref>{{cite web | author = Integrated Regional Information Networks | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2004-07-02 | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | title = Madagascar: Saving the children from Gafilo's aftermath | deadurl = no | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/madagascar/madagascar-saving-children-gafilos-aftermath | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140226232225/http://reliefweb.int/report/madagascar/madagascar-saving-children-gafilos-aftermath | archivedate = 2014-02-26 }}</ref>。

== 生态 ==
[[File:Ravenala_madagascariensis_Maui.jpg|thumb]]上有该岛标志性的[[旅人蕉|旅人蕉]]。]]
由于岛上长期与邻近大陆隔离，马达加斯加拥有的丰富动植物种类中有许多都是该国独有<ref name="CIHotSpot" /><ref name="tattersall">{{cite book | last = Tattersall | first = Ian | title = Origin of the Malagasy Strepshirhine Primates | year = 2006 | publisher = Springer | isbn = 0-387-34585-X | pages = 1-6 | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=nsBtrhsMU5EC&pg=PA3#v=onepage&q&f=false | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200708143240/https://books.google.com/books?id=nsBtrhsMU5EC&pg=PA3#v=onepage&q&f=false | archivedate = 2020-07-08 }}</ref>，近90%是[[特有种|特有种]]<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Hobbes | first1 = Joseph | last2 = Dolan | first2 = Andrew | title = World Regional Geography | publisher = Cengage Learning | location = Belmont, CA | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | year = 2008 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=yAgGHnENHjoC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false | page = 517 | isbn = 978-0-495-38950-7 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200619122625/https://books.google.com/books?id=yAgGHnENHjoC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false | archivedate = 2020-06-19 }}</ref>。如[[狐猴|狐猴]]（一种[[灵长类|灵长类]][[原猴亚目|原猴亚目]]），肉食性的[[马岛长尾狸猫|马岛长尾狸猫]]和大量[[鸟类|鸟类]]。一些生态学家因这种独特的生态系统而将马达加斯加称为“第八大洲”<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Hillstrom | first1 = Kevin | last2 = Collier Hillstrom | first2 = Laurie | title = Africa and the Middle East: a continental overview of environmental issues | publisher = ABC-CLIO | location = Santa Barbara, CA | year = 2003 | isbn = 978-1-57607-688-0 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=XxIk9zTm_e8C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | page = 50 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200708143611/https://books.google.com/books?id=XxIk9zTm_e8C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false | archivedate = 2020-07-08 }}</ref>，[[保护国际|保护国际]]也将该岛列为生物多样性热点地区<ref name="CIHotSpot">{{cite web | last = Conservation International | title = Madagascar and the Indian Ocean Islands | work = Biodiversity Hotspots | publisher = Conservation International | accessdate = 2012-03-24 | deadurl = yes | year = 2007 | url = http://www.biodiversityhotspots.org/xp/hotspots/madagascar/pages/biodiversity.aspx | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120324000527/http://www.biodiversityhotspots.org/xp/Hotspots/madagascar/pages/biodiversity.aspx | archivedate = 2012-03-24 }}</ref>。

马达加斯加拥有1万4883种植物物种，其中80%为其独有，包括5个植物科<ref name="endemism">{{cite journal | last1 = Callmander | first1 = Martin | last2 = et. al | title = The endemic and non-endemic vascular flora of Madagascar updated | journal = Plant Ecology and Evolution | volume = 144 | issue = 2 | pages = 121-125 | year = 2011 | doi = 10.5091/plecevo.2011.513 | url = http://www.mobot.org/MOBOT/Research/curators/pdf/PLECEVO_2011.pdf | format = PDF | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131103210056/http://www.mobot.org/MOBOT/Research/curators/pdf/PLECEVO_2011.pdf | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | archivedate = 2013-11-03 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。例如[[龙树科|龙树科]]包含有4个属和11个种，只存在于该国西南部的多刺灌木林中<ref name="endemicstats" />。全世界所有的[[棒锤树属|棒锤树属]]中有八成为岛上独有<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Lavranos | first1 = John | year = 2004 | title = Pachypodium makayense: A New Species From Madagascar | journal = Cactus and Succulent Journal | volume = 76 | issue = 2 | pages = 85-88}}</ref>。马达加斯加共有860种[[兰科|兰科]]植物<ref name="endemism" />，其中四分之三是特有种<ref name="Bradt" />{{rp|38}}，全世界共计8种[[猴面包树属|猴面包树属]]中就有6种只能在这里看到<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1080/106351598260879 | author=Baum DA, Small RL, Wendel JF | year = 1998 | title = Biogeography and floral evolution of baobabs (Adansonia, Bombacaceae) as inferred from multiple data sets  | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_systematic-biology_1998-06_47_2/page/181 | journal = Systematic Biology | volume = 47 | issue = 2 | pages = 181-207 | pmid = 12064226}}</ref>。岛上还有约170种棕榈科植物，相当于整个非洲大陆该科物种数的三倍，其中还有165种为独有<ref name="Bradt" />{{rp|38}}。许多原生植物都用来制成草药，可以治疗多种疾病。例如马达加斯加非常具有标志性的植物[[长春花属|马达加斯加长春花]]能够提炼出[[硫酸长春碱|硫酸长春碱]]和[[长春新碱|长春新碱]]，可以用来治疗[[霍奇金淋巴瘤|霍奇金淋巴瘤]]和[[白血病|白血病]]等多种[[癌症|癌症]]<ref name="periw">{{cite journal | last = Foster | first = Steven | title = From Herbs to Medicines: The Madagascar Periwinkle's Impact on Childhood Leukemia: A Serendipitous Discovery for Treatment | journal = Alternative and Complementary Therapies | volume = 16 | issue = 6 | pages = 347–350 | date = 2010-12 | doi = 10.1089/act.2010.16609}}</ref>。当地称为“{{lang|mg|ravinala}}”的[[旅人蕉|旅人蕉]]<ref>{{cite book  | last = Ellis | first = William | title = Three visits to Madagascar during ... 1853-1854-1856 | publisher = Oxford University | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | location = London | year = 1859 | page = 302 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=nPoGAAAAQAAJ&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>独产于该国东部雨林<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.floridata.com/ref/R/rave_mad.cfm | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131103101457/http://www.floridata.com/ref/R/rave_mad.cfm | archivedate = 2013-11-03 | title = Ravenala madagascariensis | publisher = Floridata.com | date = 2000-05-16 | last = McLendon | first = Chuck }}</ref>，该国国徽和[[马达加斯加航空|马达加斯加航空]]公司的商标上都有这种花<ref>{{cite web |last=Lambahoany Ecotourism Centre |title=Nature of Madagascar |publisher=Lambahoany Ecotourism Centre |date=2011-08-24 |url=http://www.lambahoany.org/madagascar/nature-of-madagascar/ |accessdate=2014-05-07 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103183832/http://www.lambahoany.org/madagascar/nature-of-madagascar/ |archivedate=2013-11-03 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。
[[File:OaklandZooLemurs.jpg|thumb]]就是其中之一<ref name="2009Mittermeier">{{cite journal | editor1-last = Mittermeier | editor1-first = R.A. | editor2-last = Wallis | editor2-first = J. | editor3-last = Rylands | editor3-first = A.B. | editor4-last = Ganzhorn | editor4-first = J.U. | editor5-last = Oates | editor5-first = J.F. | editor6-last = Williamson | editor6-first = E.A. | editor7-last = Palacios | editor7-first = E. | editor8-last = Heymann | editor8-first = E.W. | editor9-last = Kierulff | editor9-first = M.C.M. | editor10-last = Yongcheng | editor10-first = L. | editor11-last = Supriatna | editor11-first = J. | editor12-last = Roos | editor12-first = C. | editor13-last = Walker | editor13-first = S. | editor14-last = Cortés-Ortiz | editor14-first = L. | editor15-last = Schwitzer | editor15-first = C. | others = Illustrated by S.D. Nash | year = 2009 | title = Primates in Peril: The World's 25 Most Endangered Primates 2008–2010 | publisher = [[IUCN物种存续委员会|IUCN/SSC Primate Specialist Group]], International Primatological Society, and Conservation International | pages = 1-92 | accessdate = 2014-05-07 | url = http://www.primate-sg.org/storage/PDF/Primates.in.Peril.2008-2010.pdf | format = PDF | archivedate = 2014-02-01 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140201174835/http://www.primate-sg.org/storage/PDF/Primates.in.Peril.2008-2010.pdf | journal =  }}</ref>。]]

与植物一样，马达加斯加的动物同样种类繁多，并且有很大的比例属独有物种。保护国际称狐猴是“马达加斯加的哺乳动物旗舰物种”<ref name="CIHotSpot" />。由于没有猴等竞争对手，这一[[灵长目|灵长目]]动物已经适应了大范围的栖息环境，发展出许多个物种。截至2012年，该国经正式文献记录一共拥有[[狐猴物种列表|103个狐猴种或亚种]]<ref name="lemurextinction">{{cite news | last = Black | first = Richard | title = Lemurs sliding toward extinction | newspaper = BBC News | date = 2012-07-13 | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-18825901 | archivedate = 2014-03-05 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140305052739/http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-18825901 | accessdate = 2014-05-08 }}</ref>，其中39种是在2000到2008年间由动物学家发现的<ref name="Mittermeier2008">{{cite journal | title = Lemur diversity in Madagascar | author = Mittermeier, R.; Ganzhorn, J.; Konstant, W.; Glander, K.; Tattersall, I.; Groves, C.; Rylands, A.; Hapke, A.; Ratsimbazafy, J.; Mayor, M.; Louis, E.; Rumpler, Y.; Schwitzer, C.; Rasoloarison, R. | journal = International Journal of Primatology | doi = 10.1007/s10764-008-9317-y | pages = 1607-1656 | volume = 29 | issue = 6 | date = 2008-12}}</ref>。几乎所有的狐猴都是罕见、[[易危物种|易危]]或[[濒危物种|濒危物种]]。自人类到达马达加斯加后，已有至少17种狐猴灭绝，这些种都比幸存的种体型要大<ref>{{cite journal | author = Jungers, W.L.; Godfrey, L.R.; Simons, E.L.; Chatrath, P.S. | title = Phalangeal curvature and positional behavior in extinct sloth lemurs (Primates, Palaeopropithecidae) | journal = Procedures of the National Academy of Science (U.S.A.) | volume = 94 | issue = 22 | pages = 11998-2001 | year = 1997 | pmid = 11038588 | pmc = 23681 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.94.22.11998 | bibcode = 1997PNAS...9411998J}}</ref>。还有其他多种[[哺乳动物|哺乳动物]]属马达加斯加独有，如马岛长尾狸猫等。岛上共记载存在超过300种鸟类，其中超过60%（包括四个科，42个属）为特有种<ref name="CIHotSpot" />。还有一些科和属的[[爬行动物|爬行动物]]已在马达加斯加发展出了超过260个物种，其中90%以上属岛上独有<ref name="Okajima" />（还包括一个完全独有的科<ref name="CIHotSpot" />）。全世界所有的[[变色龙|变色龙]]种类中，有三分之二在该岛上安家落户<ref name="Okajima">{{cite journal | author = Okajima Y and Kumazawa Y | title = Mitogenomic perspectives into iguanid phylogeny and biogeography: Gondwanan vicariance for the origin of Madagascan oplurines  | journal = Gene | volume = 441 | issue = 1-2 | pages = 28-5 | year = 2009 | pmid = 18598742 | doi = 10.1016/j.gene.2008.06.011}}</ref>，其中包括已知最小的[[迷你变色龙|迷你变色龙]](與最龐大的[[帕爾森氏變色龍|帕爾森氏變色龍]])<ref>{{cite journal|title=Rivaling the World's Smallest Reptiles: Discovery of Miniaturized and Microendemic New Species of Leaf Chameleons (Brookesia) from Northern Madagascar|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0031314|url=http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0031314|date=2012-02-14|journal=PLOS ONE|volume=7|issue=2|pages=e31314|issn=1932-6203|language=en|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=Frank Glaw, Jörn Köhler, Ted M. Townsend, Miguel Vences|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503235328/http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0031314|archive-date=2018-05-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>，还有研究人员指出，马达加斯加可能是所有变色龙的发源地。该国的特有鱼类包括两个科，14个属和上百个物种，其中大部分生活在岛上的淡水湖与河流中。虽然对马达加斯加的[[无脊椎动物|无脊椎动物]]研究进展缓慢，但研究人员已经在已知物种中发现很高比例的特有种。岛上的全部651种陆栖蜗牛，以及大部分[[蝴蝶|蝴蝶]]、[[金龟子|金龟子]]、[[脉翅目|草蛉]]、[[蜘蛛|蜘蛛]]和[[蜻蜓|蜻蜓]]都是其独有物种<ref name="CIHotSpot" />。

=== 环境问题 ===
人类活动已经威胁到马达加斯加动植物的多样性<ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2011-06-28 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory?id=11291024 | title = Everglades, Madagascar Rain Forest on UNESCO List | publisher = ABC News | date = 2010-07-30 | accessdate = 2011-06-28 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110628193053/http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory?id=11291024 }}</ref>。从约2350年前人类来到岛上后，这里已经失去超过9成的[[原始森林|原始森林]]<ref>{{cite web | author = World Wildlife Fund | year = 2001 | title = Madagascar subhumid forests | work = ''WildWorld Ecoregion Profile'' | publisher = National Geographic Society | accessdate = 2011-07-28 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110728010114/http://www.nationalgeographic.com/wildworld/profiles/terrestrial/at/at0118.html | archivedate = 2011-07-28 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.nationalgeographic.com/wildworld/profiles/terrestrial/at/at0118.html }}</ref>。这些森林大部分都是由最早定居该国的人类使用一种名为“{{lang|mg|tavy}}”的[[刀耕火种|刀耕火种]]传统农业所毁<ref name="Gade 1996">{{cite journal|title=Deforestation and Its Effects in Highland Madagascar|doi=10.2307/3674005|issue=2|pages=101–116|journal=Mountain Research and Development|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/3674005|volume=16|date=1996|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=Daniel W. Gade|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428055518/https://www.jstor.org/stable/3674005|archive-date=2019-04-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。马达加斯加农民接受并继续沿用先辈的做法，这样不但能获得实际性的农业利益，还能表现文化上对繁荣、健康的向往和对祖先的尊崇<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Kull | first1 = Christian | title = Isle of Fire: The Political Ecology of Landscape Burning in Madagascar, Issue 246 | location = Chicago | publisher = University of Chicago Press | year = 2004 | url = http://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Isle_of_Fire.html?id=SCoxmSSkxn8C | isbn = 978-0-226-46141-0 | page = 153 | access-date = 2014-05-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140508075328/http://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Isle_of_Fire.html?id=SCoxmSSkxn8C | archive-date = 2014-05-08 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。从近1400年前开始，随着岛上人口密度上升，相应的破坏也随之加速<ref>{{cite journal | last = Campbell | first = Gwyn | title = The Structure of Trade in Madagascar, 1750–1810 | journal = The International Journal of African Historical Studies | volume = 26 | issue = 1 | pages = 111-148 | year = 1993 | doi = 10.2307/219188}}</ref>。到16世纪时，中部高地的原始森林已基本消失<ref name="Gade 1996" />。岛上在约1000年前引入牛群，其规模不断增长；人类一直需要使用木炭作为煮食燃料，同时咖啡在过去一个[[世纪|世纪]]里成为越来越重要的经济作物；以上多个因素共同影响，导致近年来当地森林覆盖率不断降低<ref name="spittingwind">{{cite book | last1 = Emoff | first1 = Ron | year = 2004 | title = Island Musics | chapter = Spitting into the wind: Multi-edged environmentalism in Malagasy song | editor-last = Dawe | editor-first = Kevin | publisher = Berg | location = New York | url = http://books.google.com/?id=owU3-pCIvyYC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false | isbn = 978-1-85973-703-3 | pages = 51-62 | accessdate = 2014-05-10}}</ref>。仅按保守估计，从20世纪50年代到2000年，岛上的原始森林就减少约40%，并且残余的森林密度也减少80%<ref>{{cite journal  | last1 = Harper | first1 = Grady J. | last2 = Steininger |first2 = Marc | last3 = Tucker | first3 = Compton| last4 = Juhn| first4 = Daniel | last5 = Hawkins | first5 = Frank | title = Fifty years of deforestation and forest fragmentation in Madagascar | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_environmental-conservation_2007-12_34_4/page/325 | journal = Environmental Conservation | volume = 34 | issue = 4 | pages = 325–333 | publisher = Cambridge Journals | year = 2007 | doi = 10.1017/S0376892907004262}}</ref>。野生动物保护面临重重困难，除传统农业耕种外，受保护森林也遭到非法采伐，国家还会批准对[[国家公园|国家公园]]内的珍贵木材进行采收。虽然2000至2008年间，当时的总统[[马克·拉瓦卢马纳纳|马克·拉瓦卢马纳纳]]对收集珍贵木材的行为下达了禁令，但从2009年1月起，这一做法获得新任[[国家元首|国家元首]][[安德里·拉乔利纳|安德里·拉乔利纳]]领导政府的重新授权，并且有着大幅的增长，这主要是因为拉瓦卢马纳纳下台后，马达加斯加政府获得的捐助减少，珍贵木材也就成为国家财政收入的一个主要来源<ref name="CrossroadsMarcus">{{cite web | last1 = Bachelard | first1 = Jerome | last2 = Marcus | first2 = Richard | title = Countries at the Crossroads 2011: Madagascar | publisher = Freedom House | format = PDF | year = 2011 | url = http://www.freedomhouse.org/sites/default/files/inline_images/MADAGASCARfinal.pdf | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131019043706/http://www.freedomhouse.org/sites/default/files/inline_images/MADAGASCARfinal.pdf | archivedate = 2013-10-19 | accessdate = 2013-10-19 }}</ref>。预计到2025年时，该国除保护区和东部最陡峭山坡外所有的热带雨林都将被砍伐殆尽<ref>{{cite journal | author = Green GM and Sussman RW | title = Deforestation history of the eastern rainforests of Madagascar from satellite images | journal = Science | volume = 248 |issue = 4952 | pages = 212-215 | year = 1990 | doi = 10.1126/science.248.4952.212 | bibcode = 1990Sci...248..212G | pmid = 17740137 }}</ref>。
